1. **Window.postMessage()**: This method allows a script in one window to post a message to a targetWindow (another window or frame) that is an ancestor of the targetWindow, or an element in the document of the targetWindow.

   ```javascript
// Send a message from one tab to another
window.opener.postMessage("Hello, world!", "*");

// Receive a message in another tab
window.addEventListener("message", (event) => {
  if (event.origin !== "http://example.com") return;
  console.log(event.data); // prints: "Hello, world!"
});
```

2. **SharedWorker**: SharedWorkers allow multiple windows or tabs to share the same worker thread. The worker can communicate with the windows or tabs that created it.

   ```javascript
// Create a shared worker
const worker = new SharedWorker("shared-worker.js");

// Send a message to the shared worker
worker.port.postMessage("Hello, worker!");

// Receive a message from the shared worker
worker.port.addEventListener("message", (event) => {
  console.log(event.data); // prints: "Hello, client!"
});
